# MCP Tools: Jina AI

ALWAYS include `arguments` in CallMcpTool calls. NEVER send empty `{}`.

### extract_pdf
Extract figures, tables, and equations from PDF documents using layout detection.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| id | string | No* | - | arXiv paper ID |
| url | string | No* | - | Direct PDF URL |
| max_edge | number | No | 1024 | Maximum image edge in pixels |
| type | string | No | - | Filter by figure, table, equation |

*Either id or url is required.

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "Jina AI", toolName: "extract_pdf", arguments: { id: "2301.12345", type: "figure" } })

### search_bibtex
Search for academic papers and return BibTeX citations.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| query | string | Yes | - | Paper title, topic, or keywords |
| num | number | No | 10 | Maximum results (1-50) |
| year | number | No | - | Minimum publication year |
| author | string | No | - | Author name filter |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "Jina AI", toolName: "search_bibtex", arguments: { query: "attention is all you need", num: 5 } })

### deduplicate_images
Get top-k semantically unique images using CLIP embeddings.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| images | array | Yes | - | Image URLs or base64 strings |
| k | number | No | - | Number of unique images to return |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "Jina AI", toolName: "deduplicate_images", arguments: { images: ["https://example.com/a.jpg"], k: 5 } })

### deduplicate_strings
Get top-k semantically unique strings using Jina embeddings.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| strings | array | Yes | - | Strings to deduplicate |
| k | number | No | - | Number of unique strings to return |

Example:
